title.narrative: By 2020, girls and boys, including children with disabilities, in institutions and children at risk of family separation have increased access to family and community-based alternative care

description.narrative: Significant steps were done in ensuring child's right to live and grow in a family setting: MoHSPP started transformation of the Baby Homes into Family and Child Support Centre to provide day type care services, hence preventing children from being placed in the Residential Childcare Institutions; development and strengthening gate-keeping mechanisms all over the country to address the cases of children in a child-friendly manner provided alternative family-based care options to institutions; sensitization of maternity wards' personnel to provide support to vulnerable families, to reduce risk of abandonment, relinquishment of their new-borns and to keep children with their biological families | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:16/12/2019
